                        <title ref="LIT3120Anapho">Anaphora of John Chrysostom</title>
                        <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                           ቅዳሴ፡ ዮሐንስ፡ አፈ፡ ወርቅ፡ ዘቍርባን፡ እይብል፡ ዲያቆን። ላዕለ፡ ይኩን፡ ሕሊናክሙ፡
                        </incipit>
                        <explicit xml:lang="gez">
                           ወምስለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ መንፈስ፡ ስብሐት፡ ወእኂዝ፡ ይእዜኒ፡ ወዘልፈኒ፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፨
                        </explicit>
                        <note>The text ends abruptly on <locus target="#4r"/> with the word <q xml:lang="gez">ወለሐዋር[ይቲከ]</q> and follows on <locus target="#25v"/> 
                           (cp. <bibl><ptr target="bm:Dillmann1866Chrestomathia"/><citedRange unit="page">55, l. 10</citedRange></bibl>).
                        </note>
                        
                        <msItem xml:id="p1_i1.1">
                           <locus target="#26v"/>
                           <title ref="LIT4083Prayer"></title>
                           <incipit xml:lang="gez">
                             ሐዳፌ፡ ነፍስ። ቅድመ፡ ዘቅድሳቲከ፡ ስብሐት፡ አትሐቱ፡ አግብርቲከ፡ ወአእማቲከ፡ ክሳደ፡ ነፍስ፡ ወሥጋ፡ ወመንፈስ፡
                           </incipit>
                        </msItem>
                     </msItem>

