                    <additions>
                       <list>
                          <item xml:id="a1">
                             <desc type="OwnershipNote">Ownership note</desc>
                             <locus target="#27r"/>
                             <q xml:lang="gez">
                             ዝመጽሐፍ፡ <choice><sic>ዘኣቡነ፡</sic></choice> ተክለ፡ ወንጌል፡ ዘሰረቆ፡ ወዘሄዶ፡ ውጉዘ፡ ለይኩን፡ በአፈ፡ ጴጥሮስ፡ ወጳውሎስ፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።
                             </q>
                             <note>The note states that the book belongs to<persName ref="PRS11281TaklaW">Takla Wangel</persName>.
                             </note>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="a2">
                             <desc type="GuestText">Prayer for the eucharist</desc>
                             <locus target="#27r"/>
                             <note>The prayer begins as follows:
                             <q xml:lang="gez">ሥጋ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ወደም፡ ክቡር፡ ዘእግዚእነ፡ ወመድኃኒነ፡ ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘይትወሀብ፡ ለመድኃኒት፡ ወለስርየተ፡ ኃጢኣት፡</q>, and ends as follows: 
                                <q xml:lang="gez"><add place="inline"><supplied reason="omitted">አ</supplied></add>ምን፡ አ<supplied>ምን</supplied>፡ ከመ፡ ዝንቱ፡ 
                                   ውእቱ፡ ሥ<supplied>ጋ</supplied>፡ ወደ<supplied>ም</supplied>፡ ዘበአማን፡ ሎቱ፡ ይደሉ፡ ክብር፡ ወስብሐት፡ ለዓለመ፡ ዓለም፡ አሜን።</q>.
                             </note>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="a3">
                             <desc type="MagicText">Prayer with magical names</desc>
                             <locus target="#27v"/>
                                <q xml:lang="gez">ስመ፡ አብ፡ ቡሩክ፡ ፌሌልምዩስ፡ ስመ፡ ወልድ፡ ዋሕድ፡ ኵርኵርያኖስ፡ ስመ፡ መንፈስ፡ ቅዱስ፡ ጰራቅሊጦስ፡ ጢኖጢቃኖስ፡ በዝንቱ፡ አስማቲከ፡ ይረድ፡ እመኒ፡ ልጅ፡ ወእመኒ፡ እንግዳ፡ ልጅ፡ እምዓመትከ፡ እገሊት፨</q>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="a4">
                             <desc type="GuestText">Prayer after the eucharist</desc>
                             <locus target="#27v"/>
                             <note>The prayer begins as follows:
                                <q xml:lang="gez">ኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ ዘአርአይከኒ፡ ከመ፡ ናእኩትከ፡ ወንደመር፡ ለቅዱስ፡ ሥጋከ፡ ወለቅዱስ፡ ደምከ።</q>, and ends as follows: 
                                <q xml:lang="gez">ወንትመጦ፡ እንበለ፡ ኵነኔ፡ እምሀብትከ፡ ቅድስት፡ እንተ፡ ይእቲ፡ ዘእንበለ፡ ሞት። 
                                   በኢየሱስ፡ ክርስቶስ፡ እግዚእነ፡ ዘቦቱ፡ ለከ፡ ምስሌሁ፡ ወምስለ፡ ቅዱስ፡ መንፈስ፡ ስብሐት፡ ወእኂዝ፡ ይእዜኒ፡ ወዘልፈኒ፡ ወለዓለመ፡ ዓለም።</q>.
                             </note>
                          </item>
                          
                          
                          
                          <item xml:id="e1">
                             <desc>The internal shelfmark of the Vatican Library <q xml:lang="la">Vat. | 8 | Aethiop.</q> is written on the front cover, together with the coat of arms of pope <persName ref="PRS7893PiusIX"/>.</desc>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="e2">
                             <locus target="#1r"/>
                             <desc>Titles of the works have been  added in Italian and Latin: 
                                <q xml:lang="it">
                                    <del>Miracoli della Madonna</del>
                                 </q>, <q xml:lang="la">Miracula B. M. Virg. f. 1</q>,
                                <q xml:lang="la">Organum B. M. Virg. f. 15</q>. 
                                </desc>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="e3">
                             <locus target="#1r"/>
                             <desc>The shelfmark of the Ms is added in a <date>19th century</date> hand in a little paper glued to <locus target="#1r"/>: 
                                <q xml:lang="la">Aethiop. 8</q>. 
                             </desc>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="e4">
                             <locus target="#14v"/>
                             <desc>An image, probably containing <persName ref="PRS3725Elizabet"/> and <persName ref="PRS1948Anne"/>, has been removed . 
                                Legend: <q xml:lang="gez"><choice><sic>ኤልሰቤጥ።</sic></choice> ሐና።</q>. 
                             </desc>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="e5">
                             <desc>Titles of the works have been erroneously added in Latin in a <date>16th-17th century</date> hand: 
                                <q xml:lang="la">
                                    <del>Missale Duodecim apostolorum</del>
                                 </q> (<locus target="#15r"/>), <q xml:lang="la">Missa dei</q> (<locus target="#32r"/>), 
                                <q xml:lang="la">Missa Beate Marie Virginis</q> (<locus target="#55v"/>), <q xml:lang="la">Missa ysach</q> (<locus target="#76v"/>), 
                                <q xml:lang="la">missali lingua corde u camalarin bugar</q> (<locus target="#125r"/>), <q xml:lang="la">
                                    <del>Missa Beati Gregorii pape</del>
                                 </q> (<locus target="#127r"/>).
                             </desc>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="e6">
                             <desc>The name of the owner, <persName ref="PRS11249Yaeqob">Yāʿǝqob</persName> the priest, is mentioned in several places, e.g., on <locus target="#13r #22r #158v"/>. 
                                He is mentioned together with a certain <persName ref="PRS9181TaklaMa">Takla Māryām</persName> on <locus target="#38v"/>.</desc>
                          </item>
                          
                          <item xml:id="e7">
                             <locus target="#164v"/>
                             <desc>Eight lines concerning foodstuffs are partly marked with the seal of the library and are illegible or barely legible.</desc>
                          </item>
